notes: Scorers: S Louw (South Africa) and MK Walsh (Australia)
12th Men: LJ Koen (South Africa) and BP Julian (Australia)

Cronje and Cullinan 149-run partnership in 112 mins off 166 balls; new 3rd wicket partnership record for SA in ODI's; previous record was 145 held by Cullinan and Kirsten against the UAE, Rawalpindi, 1996.
SA's total of 284 was their highest ODI score against Australia and their second highest total in SA (highest: 314/7 against NZ at Centurion, Dec 1994).
S Waugh and Bevan put on 189 for the fourth wicket - record 4th-wicket partnership for Australia in ODI's; previous record was 173 by S Waugh and D Jones against Pakistan in Perth, 1986-87.

milestones.description: Steve Waugh and Michael Bevan's 189-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 173 between Dean Jones and Steve Waugh
Hansie Cronje and Cullinan's 149-run partnership is SA's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 145 between Cullinan and Gary Kirsten
This is the highest match aggregate (571) involving teams Australia & South Africa in ODIs
